A callback is a function that is passed as an argument to 
another function and is invoked (or "called back") at a later 
time when certain operations or events have been completed.

**Callbacks are used to ensure that certain code is executed only after a specific operation has been performed

....callback are specially used for asyncronpous function

<!-- JavaScript is asynchronous by nature, -->

