<!-- call stack being full -->

1.Recursive Function Without a Base Case: A recursive function is one that calls itself. If the recursion doesn't have a base case (a condition to stop), it will keep calling itself 

2.Deeply Nested Function Calls: Even if the functions are not recursive, if you have too many deeply nested function calls, the call stack can overflow